The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                               IN THE CITY
                  
	The Cricket Association of Bengal (CAB) will be organising residential camps for the under-16, under-19 and under-22 teams as part of pre-season preparations. According to a CAB official, Kalyani, Krishnagar and Siliguri are the probable centres for the camp. Meanwhile, the CAB coaches committee will have a meeting on Tuesday where the coaches for different age groups are likely to be selected.           
	 The Bengal Olympic Association, in association with the Bengal Hockey Association and the West Bengal State Council of Sports, celebrated National Sports Day at the Town Hall. Olympian Tulsidas Balram was felicitated with the lifetime achievement award.          
	 Kaushik Pal beat Chandan Pramanik 21-10, 21-7 to reach the quarter finals of the 72nd senior state badminton championship being held at the SAI Salt Lake campus.      
	Other winners:       
	Mens singles: Arup Baidya, Subhankar Dey, Sudip Bhattacharjee; Womens singles: Sheshadri Sanyal, Amrita Mukherjee, Barnali Raha; Mens doubles: Sourav Chatterjee and Asutosh Tiwari, Arup Baidya and Kaushik Pal                
	Soccer: IFA Shield  Mohammedan Sporting vs Lajong FC at Mohun Bagan ground; Air India vs Pune FC at Howrah Stadium. Matches start at 2:45pm                                                                                                                                                                       
